HEADWORD: Redhorn
<hw>Red"horn`</hw> <pr>(-h?rn`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>Any species of a tribe of butterflies (<spn>Fugacia</spn>)
including the common yellow species and the cabbage butterflies. The
antennae are usually red.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Red-hot</ent>⟦br⟧
